tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a markedly elevated platelet distribution width (PDW), which may indicate increased platelet size variability, possibly due to platelet activation or turnover. No other hematological or lipid abnormalities are present. Correlate PDW finding clinically; if no symptoms or risk factors, this may be incidental. No acute concerns from a laboratory perspective.
